# Welcome to RenderMark

**Markdown** was created by [John Gruber](https://daringfireball.net/) in 2004, with significant contributions from Aaron Swartz. The goal was simple: create a plain text formatting syntax that's easy to read and write, and can be converted to HTML.

![Markdown](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/57/Markdown-mark-purple.svg)

## Why Markdown?

Markdown has become the *de facto* standard for writing on the web. Here's why it's so popular:

- **Readable** — The syntax is designed to look good as plain text
- **Portable** — Works everywhere, from GitHub to Slack to your notes app
- **Future-proof** — Plain text files will always be readable

## Text Formatting

You can make text **bold** or *italic* or even ***both***. You can also ~~strikethrough~~ text.

A full markdown reference can be found [here](https://rendermark.app/markdown-cheatsheet).

